# Development Rules

## Principles
- **YAGNI**: Don't implement what you don't need yet
- **KISS**: Simplest solution that works
- **DRY**: Extract shared logic, don't copy-paste

## File Standards
- **Naming**: kebab-case files (`login-form.tsx`, `token-store.ts`); PascalCase for React components
- **Size**: Split large files into focused modules (features vs pages vs components)
- **Comments**: Only where logic isn't self-evident. No obvious comments

## Code Quality
- Handle errors explicitly — surface `ApiError` messages to users; don't swallow failures silently
- No hardcoded secrets, API keys, or credentials
- Validate forms with Zod schemas in `src/auth/schemas.ts` (or feature-local schemas)
- Prefer early returns over deep nesting
- Use TypeScript strictly — avoid `any`; prefer typed API envelopes from `src/api/types.ts`

## Implementation Rules
- Read existing code before modifying — understand patterns first
- Update existing files; don't create "enhanced" copies
- After modifying code, run `npm run build` or `make check` to verify
- Don't over-engineer: no feature flags or backwards-compat shims for unused code
- Three similar lines > premature abstraction

## Pre-commit
- Run `make lint` and `make build` before push
- Update `src/api/types.ts` when backend API shapes change
- Never commit `.env`, credentials, or secrets
